<sect1 id="dir_50a13eed33dcd9f476e4986821866285_1autotoc_md560">
<title>helios::engine::runtime::pooling</title><para>GameObject pooling for efficient object recycling.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_50a13eed33dcd9f476e4986821866285_1autotoc_md561">
<title>Overview</title><para>This module provides infrastructure for memory-efficient entity management through object pooling. Pools pre-allocate GameObjects that can be acquired and released during gameplay, avoiding repeated allocation overhead.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_50a13eed33dcd9f476e4986821866285_1autotoc_md562">
<title>Key Classes</title><para><table rows="6" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Class  </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Purpose  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>GameObjectPool</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Container holding pre-allocated GameObject identifiers with O(1) acquire/release  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>GameObjectPoolConfig</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Configuration data for pool initialization (ID, prefab, size)  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>GameObjectPoolManager</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>High-level manager for pool lifecycle and acquire/release operations  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>GameObjectPoolRegistry</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Central registry mapping pool IDs to pool instances  </para>
</entry></row>
